;         &mut is encoded with a (current,final) prophecy datatype `mut<Int>`.
;         Proving the program safe = proving this system `sat` (an inductive
;         invariant exists). The needed invariant is simple/linear
;         (final(*a) = initial(*a) + i).
;
; Invocation (exact args Thrust uses):
;     z3 fp.spacer.global=true fp.validate=true  this_file.smt2
;   (also reproduces with NO args, and with fp.spacer.global=false.)
;
; Observed:
;     z3 4.13.0  -> sat   ~0.3s
;     z3 4.13.4  -> sat   ~0.3s
;     z3 4.14.0  -> sat   ~0.3s
;     z3 4.14.1  -> sat   ~0.3s
;     z3 4.15.0  -> sat   ~0.2s
;     z3 4.15.2  -> sat   ~0.2s
;     z3 4.16.0  -> (no answer within 180s; effectively hangs)   <-- REGRESSION
;
;   17 Spacer option combinations tried on 4.16.0 — all time out.
;   CoAR/PCSat solves it in ~5-19s, so the system itself is satisfiable.
;
; Regression window: introduced between z3 4.15.2 and 4.16.0.
; ============================================================================

